object: William Jerome Bichsel, S.J. (May 26, 1928 – February 28, 2015), nicknamed "Bix", was Jesuit priest in Tacoma, Washington, United States. He is notable for his actions as a non-violent protester, spending time in federal prison for demonstrating on issues such as nuclear weapons and the School of the Americas.
